I" <p>I recently finished my first prototype for a dedicated computer music system for vibraphone, just in time to use it at 
<a href="http://www.electrofringe.net/">Electrofringe</a> at the end of September and to take with me to Sweden!</p>

<p>The idea is to have a battery powered computer system that can attach to a vibraphone, includes a microphone for processing the vibraphone sound and can output straight to the mixing desk at a gig.</p>

<p><img src="/squarespace_images/2011-10-28-CMSVibes1.jpg" alt="The whole system fits on the end of my vibraphone - compact!" /></p>

<p>The whole system fits on the end of my vibraphone - compact!</p>

<p>The current setup has:</p>

<ul>
  <li>4 electret microphones that blutack under the damper pedal in the vibraphone.</li>
  <li>A <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Handmade-Electronic-Music-Hardware-Hacking/dp/0415998735/ref=dp_ob_title_bk">battery powered preamp and power supply</a> for the microphones that mixes them down to a mono signal.</li>
  <li>An <a href="http://www.ikmultimedia.com/irig/features/">IK Multimedia iRig</a> dongle to make it easier to connect the microphones and the output to an iPhone</li>
  <li>an iPhone (or iPad) running RjDJ</li>
  <li><a href="http://rjdj.me/music/Charles%20Martin/Norra%20Vinter/399/">my own custom RjDJ scene</a> (programmed in Pd).</li>
  <li>A <a href="http://www.behringer.com/EN/Products/DI20.aspx">cheap stereo DI box</a> to minimise the work that a sound technician has to do before I can plug into the desk.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/squarespace_images/2011-10-28-CMSVibes2.jpg" alt="The microphones on the bottom of the damper bar." /> The microphones on the bottom of the damper bar.
<img src="/squarespace_images/2011-10-28-CMSVibes3.jpg" alt="" /> <br />
