<h3 id="updated-2012-11-04">Updated! 2012-11-04</h3>

<p>So Iâ€™ve had a few questions about how to make the actual microphones. I donâ€™t have good pictures to go into a total tutorial, but the microphones themselves are cheap <a href="http://www.jaycar.com.au/productView.asp?ID=AM4011&amp;keywords=electret+mics&amp;form=KEYWORD">electret capsules</a>, connected to a long audio cable and then to a simple power supply circuit.</p>

<p>There are good walkthroughs about the power supply circuit in the free version of <a href="http://www.nicolascollins.com/texts/originalhackingmanual.pdf">Hardware Hacking</a> and on this <a href="http://webpages.charter.net/tidmarsh/binmic/">website</a>.</p>

<p>Have fun!</p>
